cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to classify news articles as fake or credible. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. 

The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to collect the dataset, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the second likely sub-category. 

The use of machine learning algorithms to classify news articles falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the third likely sub-category. 

The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to identify patterns in the data, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the fourth likely sub-category. 

Finally, the paper discusses the implications of fake news on social media, which suggests cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the fifth likely sub-category.
